  11:/Users/ozalp/Documents/DaisyExamples/libDaisy/src/per/sai.h ****  * Allows for master or slave, as well as freedom of selecting direction, 
  12:/Users/ozalp/Documents/DaisyExamples/libDaisy/src/per/sai.h ****  * and other behavior for each peripheral, and block.
  13:/Users/ozalp/Documents/DaisyExamples/libDaisy/src/per/sai.h ****  * 
  14:/Users/ozalp/Documents/DaisyExamples/libDaisy/src/per/sai.h ****  * DMA Transfer commands must use buffers located within non-cached memory or use cache maintenance
  15:/Users/ozalp/Documents/DaisyExamples/libDaisy/src/per/sai.h ****  * To declare an unitialized global element in the DMA memory section:
  16:/Users/ozalp/Documents/DaisyExamples/libDaisy/src/per/sai.h ****  *    int32_t DSY_DMA_BUFFER_SECTOR my_buffer[96];
  17:/Users/ozalp/Documents/DaisyExamples/libDaisy/src/per/sai.h ****  *
